Size


Zend\Validator\File\Size
 checks for the size of a file.


Supported Options


The following set of options are supported:




min
: Minimum file size in integer bytes, or in string SI notation; 
null

  indicates no minimum required.


max
: maximum file size in integer bytes, or in string SI notation; 
null

  indicates no maximum required.


useByteString
: Boolean flag indicating whether to dispaly error messages
  using SI notation (default, 
true
), or in bytes (
false
).




SI units supported are: kB, MB, GB, TB, PB, and EB. All sizes are converted
using 1024 as the base value (ie. 1kB == 1024 bytes, 1MB == 1024kB).


